		<td width="72%" style="font-family: arial,sans-serif; color: #000" valign="top">
		<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0" align="center"><b>
		<span style="letter-spacing: -0.15pt">
		<font face="Arial" color="#800000">Curriculum vitae: </font></span>
		<span style="letter-spacing: -.15pt">
			<font face="Arial" color="#800000">Edward N. Peters, JD, JCD</font></span></b><p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0" align="center">
		<span style="letter-spacing: -0.15pt"><b>
		<font face="Arial" size="1" color="#800000">&nbsp;</font></b></span><p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		<font face="Arial">
		Edward 
		Peters has doctoral degrees in American law from the University of 
		Missouri at Columbia and in canon law from the Catholic University of 
		America. After over a decade in diocesan canonical administration, Dr. 
		Peters joined the faculty at Sacred Heart Major Seminary in Detroit 
		where he now teaches. His articles and reviews have appeared in scores 
		of publications around the world and he serves as an advisor to a wide 
		variety of ecclesiastical institutions and persons. Dr. Peters administers 
		<a target="_blank" href="index.html" style="text-decoration: none">
		Canonlaw.info</a>, the internet's largest canon law resource. He and 
		his wife Angela have raised six children.</font><p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		<font face="Arial" size="1">&nbsp;</font></td>
		<td width="15%" style="font-family: arial,sans-serif; color: #000">
		<p align="center">
		<font face="Arial">
		<img border="0" src="zzedp2014.JPG" width="115" height="146"></font></td>
	</tr>
